        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Thousands march on Karachi</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Thousands of supporters of former Pakistani Prime Minister Imran Khan <a href="https://apnews.com/article/pakistan-lockdown-imran-khan-rally-clashes-belarus-ec6cb96753c83be24b20cd32588ead71" target="_blank">defied</a> heavy police resistance, lockdown measures, and widespread arrests to march toward Islamabad, demanding his release. Clashes with authorities left one police officer dead and several others injured, while tear gas and roadblocks failed to deter the protesters.
          Khan’s Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) party led the march, with his wife, Bushra Bibi, addressing crowds 30 miles from the capital. Protesters vowed to overcome obstacles, including police barricades, to reach their goal.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-19844270" target="_blank">Khan</a>, jailed since August 2023, faces over 150 criminal cases, which his party claims are politically motivated. The march coincided with a visit by Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko, further intensifying tensions. The government criticized the demonstrations for harming Pakistan’s fragile economy, with analysts warning of significant financial losses.</p>
        </mj-text>
